{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #955: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let\\[s(n)=\\sigma(n)-n=\\sum_{\\substack{d\\mid n\\\\ d<n}}d\\]be the sum of proper divisors function.\n\nIf $A\\subset \\mathbb{N}$ has density $0$ then $s^{-1}(A)$ must also have density $0$. Current best: Pollack, Pomerance, and Thompson \\cite{PPT18} prove that if $\\epsilon(x)=o(1)$ and $A\\subset \\mathbb{N}$ has size at most $x^{1/2+\\epsilon(x)}$ then\\[\\#\\{ n\\leq x: s(n)\\in A\\} =o(x)\\]as $x\\to \\infty$. It follows that (using $s(n)\\ll n\\log\\log n$) if $A$ grows like $\\lvert A\\cap [1,x]\\rvert\\leq x^{1/2+o(1)}$ then $s^{-1}(A)$ has density $0$. Prize: no. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_05fdf473f4c1a4e2","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: FC 955 (PR #4352) [in-pr] https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures/pull/4352.","id":"vf_f619eafe8a01108f","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/955.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_05fdf473f4c1a4e2","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:955","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_f619eafe8a01108f","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:955","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_f619eafe8a01108f","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"vf_05fdf473f4c1a4e2"